Package: SynTruthPkg
Type: Package
Title: Create synthetic data of gene expression, treatment and survival to test algorithms for predicting treatment response. 
Version: 0.1.0
Author: c(person("Dora", "Schuller", email = "schuller.dora@gmail.com",
  role = c("aut", "cre")),
  person("Rowan", "Kuiper", email = "r.kuiper@skylinedx.com", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Dora Schuller <schuller.dora@gmail.com>
Description: A framework for creating synthetic datasets of gene expression, treatment and survival. 
     Contains functions to analyze the synthetic data. 
     SynTruth_guide.Rmd walks you through all the functions.
     Find out more about the package in Dora Schuller's thesis. Ask Domenico Bellomo (d.bellomo@skylinedx.com) for the thesis.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.1)
